A ranar Lahadi, Fadar White House ta ce Donald Trump zai iya "dakatar da wani mako" na babban alhakin ganawa da mataimakin attorney janar Rod Rosenstein, yayin da ake ci gaba da gwagwarmayar neman takarar kotun koli Brett Kavanaugh.
Rosenstein yana kula da aikin Robert Mueller, mai ba da shawara na musamman, wanda ke binciken alaƙar da ke tsakanin mataimakan Trump da Rasha da kuma tsoma baki a shari'a ta shugaban kasa saboda tsoma bakin Rasha a zaben.
Washington ta yi ta shagaltar da labarai na watanni da yawa game da ko Trump zai yi wa mataimakin attorney janar zagon kasa, kuma ya sanya 'yancin Muller cikin hadari saboda hakan.
A farkon wannan watan, kamar yadda jaridar New York Times ta ruwaito, Rosenstein ya tattauna yiwuwar kawar da shugaban kasa ta hanyar 25th Amendment don yin rikodin tattaunawa da Trump.
Rosenstein ya musanta rahoton.
Amma a ranar Litinin da ta gabata, ya tafi fadar White House duk da cewa an yi hasashen cewa zai yi murabus.
Maimakon haka, an sanar da taron da za a yi da Trump a ranar Alhamis, a Majalisar Dinkin Duniya da ke New York.
Trump ya ce "ba zai fi son" a harbe Rosenstein ba amma an jinkirta taron don kauce wa rikici da kotun majalisa na majalisa, wanda Kavanagh da Dr. Christine Blasey Ford, daya daga cikin matan da suka yi zargin cin zarafin, sun gabatar da shaida.
A ranar Juma'a, Trump ya ba da umarnin bincike na mako guda na FBI game da ikirarin da aka yi wa Kavanagh, yana kara jinkirta cikakken kuri'ar Senate.
Sakatariyar yada labarai ta Trump, Sarah Sanders, ta bayyana a Fox News a ranar Lahadi.
Da aka tambaye shi game da taron Rosenstein, ya ce: "Ba a sanya kwanan wata ba, zai iya zama wannan makon, kuma zan iya ganin an sake tura shi mako guda, idan aka ba da duk sauran abubuwan da ke faruwa a Kotun Koli.
